radiotherapy at the end of 2 years of age at least. The total mortality 
(surgical deaths: 7 cases) and deaths during the follow-up period (11 cases) was 
38.5%. Out of the 24 surviving children, 8 (20%) are normal: 7 (17%) exhibit 
only minimal neurosurgical deficits; 9 (22%) are seriously handicapped. One 
child has been lost for the follow-up observation.

