The absence of a complex qualitative instrument for measuring population health 
hinders in assessing public health efficacy at the local level. There is 
introduced a principally new approach to the determination of health 
characteristics at the starting level proceeding from the exhausted viability. 
Impairments of viability are classified according to the cycles of human 
